      <bioghist>
         <head>Biographical/Historical Information</head>
         <p>William B. Alexander was a cabinetmaker and waggoner in
         Augusta County, Virginia.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent>
         <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
         <p>Includes a memorandum book, covering the years 1842 and
         1846-1871, which lists 803 coffins, including names, death
         dates, and causes of death (Accession 29658a), as well as a
         ledger (Accession 29658b) which covers the years 1850-1888 and
         1921.</p>
      </scopecontent>
